 <code>ite</code>, so it doesn't work. Does anyone have any suggestions on how to prove this? Or what <code>continuous_on.dif</code> would look like?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">topology.unit_interval</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">open_locale</span> <span class=\"n\">unit_interval</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">noncomputable theory</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">two_mul_mem_I</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ht0</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ht</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚àà</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"o\">‚ü®</span><span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">linarith</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">linarith</span><span class=\"o\">‚ü©</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">two_sub_two_mul_mem_I</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ht</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\"